---
Ciphers are rogue-type practitioners specializing in infiltration, intelligence, and bypassing institutional controls.
The tradition formed after the Ninth Meridian Catastrophe among route guides, fence operators, and intelligence dealers.
No formal guild exists. Knowledge transmits through oral apprenticeship outside legitimate institutions.
Core insight: every system of control creates its own perimeter, and every perimeter has a gap.
Combat role is indirect. Ciphers excel at evasion, information gathering, and exploiting systemic weaknesses.
Key abilities involve lockpicking, document forgery, seal duplication, and stealth movement.
The Saltglass Reach coastal zone is the primary operating corridor with three trade routes.
The tradition operates outside the Violet Compact's registry framework with no governance structure.
Ciphers share foundational skills with the Warlock tradition, which builds on cipher shadow-work.
